&lt;p&gt;Northumbria Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust is proud to be working in partnership with Sunderland Medical School. Sunderland Medical School began in September 2019 and in September 2021 the first cohort of year 3 students will begin their placement in Northumbria Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Medical Education Coordinator to join the team to help plan and implement the Sunderland Medical School curriculum within Northumbria Trust. The Medical Education Coordinator post is a rewarding and challenging role with varied work involved. You will work closely with the Medical Education Manager and the Director for Undergraduate Curriculum Studies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is focused on the planning and implementation of the Sunderland curriculum in the trust ready for the medical students joining us in September 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is fixed term for 12 months, Part Time 7.5 hours per week. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Tracey Hogg&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Medical Education Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Tracey.Hogg3@northumbria-healthcare.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07967 814 544&lt;/p&gt;
